short_description: HaeIII methylase was allowed to mutate under genetic drift for 3, 7, and 17 generations. The authors report the frequency of mutants in the post-drift population relative to wild-type, suggesting selective pressure. The study's wild-type has 5 mutations relative to UniProt sequence for the gene (P20589): C26A, I104K, M115L, F181L, C327R. [MAVEdb note: The 5 background mutants have been appended to each of the author's single mutants.]
